This video spreads disinformation about COVID and its transmission upon the death of someone infected with the virus. In light of the controversial Sri Lankan policy prohibiting burials which has been condemned due to it infringing upon the religious freedom of Muslims and Christians, this video repeats the disinformation that has been used to discredit the scientific basis under which burials are in fact permitted, positing that burials would result in the spread of COVID (14:50-26:18). The video has garnered a lot of attention. The creator is a prolific tuition teacher in Sri Lanka, and therefore it is highly likely that this video is received and shared as a credible authority. Accordingly, the disinformation spread by this video has dangerous implications in light of an already volatile political issue that has galvanized certain nationalist, anti-minority elements. The latest report by an independent panel of experts has reinstated that burials could and should be permitted in Sri Lanka: https://www.colombotelegraph.com/index.php/cremation-vs-burial-expert-panel-revises-recommendation-to-include-both-cremation-and-burial-of-covid-19-dead-bodies/
